Cable.description: The `Cable` schema contains properties that describe a cable connecting endpoints of a chassis, port, or any other cable-compatible endpoint.
Cable.longDescription: This resource contains a simple cable for a Redfish implementation.

@odata.context.description: The OData description of a payload.
@odata.context.longDescription: The value of this property shall be the context URL that describes the resource according to OData-Protocol and shall be of the form defined in the Redfish specification.

@odata.etag.description: The current ETag of the resource.
@odata.etag.longDescription: The value of this property shall be a string that is defined by the ETag HTTP header definition in RFC7232.

@odata.id.description: The unique identifier for a resource.
@odata.id.longDescription: The value of this property shall be the unique identifier for the resource and it shall be of the form defined in the Redfish specification.

@odata.type.longDescription: The value of this property shall be a URI fragment that specifies the type of the resource and it shall be of the form defined in the Redfish specification.

Actions.description: The available actions for this resource.
Actions.longDescription: This property shall contain the available actions for this resource.

Assembly.description: The link to the assembly associated with this cable.
Assembly.longDescription: This property shall contain a link to a resource of type `Assembly`.

AssetTag.description: The user-assigned asset tag for this cable.
AssetTag.longDescription: This property shall track the cable for inventory purposes.

CableClass.description: The identifier for the downstream resource.
CableClass.longDescription: The property shall contain the cable class for this cable.

CableStatus.description: The user-reported status of this resource.
CableStatus.longDescription: This property shall contain the user-reported status of this resource.

CableType.longDescription: This property shall contain a user-defined type for this cable.

anyOf.description: The description of this resource.  Used for commonality in the schema definitions.
anyOf.longDescription: This property shall contain the description of this resource.  The value shall conform with the 'Description' clause of the Redfish Specification.

DownstreamConnectorTypes.description: The connector types this cable supports.
DownstreamConnectorTypes.longDescription: The property shall contain an array of connector types this cable supports.

DownstreamName.description: The identifier for the downstream resource.
DownstreamName.longDescription: This property shall contain any identifier for a downstream resource.

LengthMeters.description: The length of the cable in meters.
LengthMeters.longDescription: This property shall contain the length of the cable in meters.

Links.description: The links to other resources that are related to this resource.
Links.longDescription: This property shall contain links to resources that are related to but are not contained by, or subordinate to, this resource.

Location.longDescription: This property shall contain the location information of the associated assembly.

Manufacturer.longDescription: This property shall contain the name of the organization responsible for producing the cable.  This organization might be the entity from whom the cable is purchased, but this is not necessarily true.

Model.description: The model number of the cable.
Model.longDescription: This property shall contain the name by which the manufacturer generally refers to the cable.

Oem.longDescription: This property shall contain the OEM extensions.  All values for properties that this object contains shall conform to the Redfish Specification-described requirements.

PartNumber.description: The part number for this cable.
PartNumber.longDescription: This property shall contain the part number assigned by the organization that is responsible for producing or manufacturing the cable.

SKU.longDescription: This property shall contain the stock-keeping unit (SKU) number for this cable.

SerialNumber.description: The serial number for this cable.
SerialNumber.longDescription: This property shall contain the manufacturer-allocated number that identifies the cable.

Status.description: The status and health of the resource and its subordinate or dependent resources.
Status.longDescription: This property shall contain any status or health properties of the resource.

UpstreamConnectorTypes.description: The connector types this cable supports.
UpstreamConnectorTypes.longDescription: The property shall contain an array of connector types this cable supports.

UpstreamName.description: The identifier for the downstream resource.
UpstreamName.longDescription: This property shall contain any identifier for an upstream resource.

UserDescription.longDescription: This property shall contain a user-defined description for this cable.

UserLabel.longDescription: This property shall contain a user-assigned label used to identify this resource.  If a value has not been assigned by a user, the value of this property shall be an empty string.

Vendor.longDescription: This property shall contain the name of the company that provides the final product that includes this cable.

enumDescriptions.Fabric: This cable is used for connecting to a fabric.
enumDescriptions.Fan: This cable is used for connecting to a fan system.
enumDescriptions.General: This cable is used for providing general connectivity.
enumDescriptions.Network: This cable is used for connecting to a networking system.
enumDescriptions.PCIe: This cable is used for connecting to a PCIe endpoint.
enumDescriptions.Power: This cable is used for connecting to a power system.
enumDescriptions.Serial: This cable is used for connecting to a serial endpoint.
enumDescriptions.Storage: This cable is used for connecting to a storage system.
enumDescriptions.USB: This cable is used for connecting to a USB endpoint.
enumDescriptions.Video: This cable is used for connecting to a video system.

enumDescriptions.SetByService: The cable status is set by the service.

enumLongDescriptions.Degraded: This value shall indicate the cable is degraded.  The `State` property in `Status` shall contain the value `Enabled` and the `Health` property in `Status` shall contain the value `Warning`.
enumLongDescriptions.Disabled: This value shall indicate the cable is disabled.  The `State` property in `Status` shall contain the value `Disabled`.
enumLongDescriptions.Failed: This value shall indicate the cable has failed.  The `State` property in `Status` shall contain the value `Enabled` and the `Health` property in `Status` shall contain the value `Critical`.
enumLongDescriptions.Normal: This value shall indicate the cable is operating normally.  The `State` property in `Status` shall contain the value `Enabled` and the `Health` property in `Status` shall contain the value `OK`.
enumLongDescriptions.SetByService: This value shall indicate the status for the cable is not defined by the user.  If implemented, the service shall determine the value of the `State` and `Health` properties in `Status`.
enumLongDescriptions.Testing: This value shall indicate the cable is under test.  The `State` property in `Status` shall contain the value `InTest`.

enumDescriptions.ACPower: This cable connects to an AC power connector.
enumDescriptions.CDFP: This cable connects to a CDFP connector.
enumDescriptions.DB9: This cable connects to a DB9 connector.
enumDescriptions.DCPower: This cable connects to a DC power connector.
enumDescriptions.DisplayPort: This cable connects to a DisplayPort power connector.
enumDescriptions.HDMI: This cable connects to an HDMI connector.
enumDescriptions.ICI: This cable connects to an ICI connector.
enumDescriptions.IPASS: This cable connects to an IPASS connector.
enumDescriptions.OSFP: This cable connects to an OSFP connector.
enumDescriptions.PCIe: This cable connects to a PCIe connector.
enumDescriptions.Proprietary: This cable connects to a proprietary connector.
enumDescriptions.QSFP: This cable connects to a QSFP connector.
enumDescriptions.RJ45: This cable connects to an RJ45 connector.
enumDescriptions.SATA: This cable connects to a SATA connector.
enumDescriptions.SCSI: This cable connects to a SCSI connector.
enumDescriptions.SFP: This cable connects to an SFP connector.
enumDescriptions.SFPPlus: This cable connects to an SFPPlus connector.
enumDescriptions.SlimSAS: This cable connects to a SlimSAS connector.
enumDescriptions.USBA: This cable connects to a USB-A connector.
enumDescriptions.USBC: This cable connects to a USB-C connector.

Links.description: The links to other resources that are related to this resource.
Links.longDescription: This Redfish Specification-described type shall contain links to resources that are related to but are not contained by, or subordinate to, this resource.

DownstreamChassis.description: An array of links to the downstream chassis connected to this cable.
DownstreamChassis.longDescription: This property shall contain an array of links to resources of type `Chassis` that represent the physical downstream containers connected to this cable.

items.description: The `Chassis` schema represents the physical components of a system.  This resource represents the sheet-metal confined spaces and logical zones such as racks, enclosures, chassis and all other containers.  Subsystems, such as sensors, that operate outside of a system's data plane are linked either directly or indirectly through this resource.  A subsystem that operates outside of a system's data plane are not accessible to software that runs on the system.  It also describes the location, such as a slot, socket, or bay, where a unit can be installed, by populating a resource instance with an absent state if a unit is not present.
items.longDescription: This resource shall represent a chassis or other physical enclosure for a Redfish implementation.  It may also represent a location, such as a slot, socket, or bay, where a unit may be installed, but the `State` property within the `Status` property contains `Absent`.

anyOf.description: A reference to a resource.
anyOf.longDescription: The value of this property shall be used for references to a resource.

Actions.description: The available actions for this resource.
Actions.longDescription: This property shall contain the available actions for this resource.

AssetTag.description: The user-assigned asset tag of this chassis.
AssetTag.longDescription: This property shall contain an identifying string that tracks the chassis for inventory purposes.  Modifying this property may modify the `AssetTag` in the resource that represents the functional view of this chassis, such as a `ComputerSystem` resource.

ChassisType.description: The type of physical form factor of the chassis.
ChassisType.longDescription: This property shall indicate the physical form factor for the type of chassis.

IndicatorLED.description: The state of the indicator LED, which identifies the chassis.
IndicatorLED.longDescription: This property shall contain the indicator light state for the indicator light associated with this system.

enumDescriptions.Unknown: The state of the indicator LED cannot be determined.

enumLongDescriptions.Blinking: This value shall represent the indicator LED is in a blinking state where the LED is being turned on and off in repetition.  If the service does not support this value, it shall reject `PATCH` or `PUT` requests containing this value by returning the HTTP `400 Bad Request` status code.
enumLongDescriptions.Lit: This value shall represent the indicator LED is in a solid on state.  If the service does not support this value, it shall return the HTTP `400 Bad Request` status code to reject `PATCH` or `PUT` requests that contain this value.
enumLongDescriptions.Off: This value shall represent the indicator LED is in a solid off state.  If the service does not support this value, it shall reject `PATCH` or `PUT` requests containing this value by returning the HTTP `400 Bad Request` status code.
enumLongDescriptions.Unknown: This value shall represent the indicator LED is in an unknown state.  The service shall reject `PATCH` or `PUT` requests containing this value by returning the HTTP `400 Bad Request` status code.

Model.description: The model number of the chassis.

Oem.longDescription: This property shall contain the OEM extensions.  All values for properties that this object contains shall conform to the Redfish Specification-described requirements.

PartNumber.description: The part number of the chassis.
PartNumber.longDescription: This property shall contain a part number assigned by the organization that is responsible for producing or manufacturing the chassis.

Power.description: The link to the power properties, or power supplies, power policies, and sensors, for this chassis.
Power.longDescription: This property shall contain a link to a resource of type `Power` that represents the power characteristics of this chassis.

PowerState.description: The current power state of the chassis.
PowerState.longDescription: This property shall contain the power state of the chassis.

enumDescriptions.Off: The resource is powered off.  The components within the resource might continue to have AUX power.
enumDescriptions.PoweringOff: A temporary state between on and off.  The components within the resource can take time to process the power off action.
enumDescriptions.PoweringOn: A temporary state between off and on.  The components within the resource can take time to process the power on action.

SKU.longDescription: This property shall contain the stock-keeping unit number for this chassis.

SerialNumber.description: The serial number of the chassis.
SerialNumber.longDescription: This property shall contain a manufacturer-allocated number that identifies the chassis.

Status.description: The status and health of the resource and its subordinate or dependent resources.
Status.longDescription: This property shall contain any status or health properties of the resource.

Thermal.description: The link to the thermal properties, such as fans, cooling, and sensors, for this chassis.
Thermal.longDescription: This property shall contain a link to a resource of type `Thermal` that represents the thermal characteristics of this chassis.

anyOf.description: The `Chassis` schema represents the physical components of a system.  This resource represents the sheet-metal confined spaces and logical zones such as racks, enclosures, chassis and all other containers.  Subsystems, such as sensors, that operate outside of a system's data plane are linked either directly or indirectly through this resource.  A subsystem that operates outside of a system's data plane are not accessible to software that runs on the system.  It also describes the location, such as a slot, socket, or bay, where a unit can be installed, by populating a resource instance with an absent state if a unit is not present.
anyOf.longDescription: This resource shall represent a chassis or other physical enclosure for a Redfish implementation.  It may also represent a location, such as a slot, socket, or bay, where a unit may be installed, but the `State` property within the `Status` property contains `Absent`.

anyOf.description: The `Chassis` schema represents the physical components of a system.  This resource represents the sheet-metal confined spaces and logical zones such as racks, enclosures, chassis and all other containers.  Subsystems, such as sensors, that operate outside of a system's data plane are linked either directly or indirectly through this resource.  A subsystem that operates outside of a system's data plane are not accessible to software that runs on the system.  It also describes the location, such as a slot, socket, or bay, where a unit can be installed, by populating a resource instance with an absent state if a unit is not present.

anyOf.description: The `Chassis` schema represents the physical components of a system.  This resource represents the sheet-metal confined spaces and logical zones such as racks, enclosures, chassis and all other containers.  Subsystems, such as sensors, that operate outside of a system's data plane are linked either directly or indirectly through this resource.  A subsystem that operates outside of a system's data plane are not accessible to software that runs on the system.  It also describes the location, such as a slot, socket, or bay, where a unit can be installed, by populating a resource instance with an absent state if a unit is not present.
anyOf.longDescription: This resource shall represent a chassis or other physical enclosure for a Redfish implementation.  It may also represent a location, such as a slot, socket, or bay, where a unit may be installed, but the `State` property within the `Status` property contains `Absent`.

Assembly.description: The link to the assembly associated with this chassis.
Assembly.longDescription: This property shall contain a link to a resource of type `Assembly`.

AssetTag.description: The user-assigned asset tag of this chassis.
AssetTag.longDescription: This property shall contain an identifying string that tracks the chassis for inventory purposes.  Modifying this property may modify the `AssetTag` in the resource that represents the functional view of this chassis, such as a `ComputerSystem` resource.

Certificates.description: The link to a collection of certificates for device identity and attestation.
Certificates.longDescription: This property shall contain a link to a resource collection of type `CertificateCollection` that contains certificates for device identity and attestation.

ChassisType.description: The type of physical form factor of the chassis.
ChassisType.longDescription: This property shall indicate the physical form factor for the type of chassis.

Controls.description: The link to the collection of controls located in this chassis.
Controls.longDescription: This property shall contain a link to a resource collection of type `ControlCollection`.

DepthMm.longDescription: This property shall represent the depth (length) of the chassis, in millimeter units, as specified by the manufacturer.

Drives.description: The link to the collection of drives within this chassis.
Drives.longDescription: This property shall contain a link to a resource collection of type `DriveCollection`.

ElectricalSourceManagerURIs.description: The URIs of the management interfaces for the external electrical source connections for this chassis.
ElectricalSourceManagerURIs.longDescription: This property shall contain an array of URIs to the management applications or devices that provide monitoring or control of the external electrical sources that provide power to this chassis.

ElectricalSourceNames.description: The names of the external electrical sources, such as circuits or outlets, connected to this chassis.
ElectricalSourceNames.longDescription: This property shall contain an array of strings that identify the external electrical sources, such as the names of circuits or outlets, that provide power to this chassis.

EnvironmentMetrics.description: The link to the environment metrics for this chassis.
EnvironmentMetrics.longDescription: This property shall contain a link to a resource of type `EnvironmentMetrics` that specifies the environment metrics for this chassis, all containing chassis, and devices contained by any of these chassis instances.  When determining power and energy readings, care should be taken to ensure any reported values do not overlap or result in double-counting.

EnvironmentalClass.description: The ASHRAE Environmental Class for this chassis.
EnvironmentalClass.longDescription: This property shall contain the ASHRAE Environmental Class for this chassis, as defined by ASHRAE Thermal Guidelines for Data Processing Environments.  These classes define respective environmental limits that include temperature, relative humidity, dew point, and maximum allowable elevation.

FabricAdapters.longDescription: This property shall contain a link to a resource collection of type `FabricAdapterCollection` that represents fabric adapters in this chassis that provide access to fabric-related resource pools.

HeightMm.longDescription: This property shall represent the height of the chassis, in millimeter units, as specified by the manufacturer.

HotPluggable.description: An indication of whether this component can be inserted or removed while the equipment is in operation.
HotPluggable.longDescription: This property shall indicate whether the component can be inserted or removed while the underlying equipment otherwise remains in its current operational state.  Components indicated as hot-pluggable shall allow the component to become operable without altering the operational state of the underlying equipment.  Components that cannot be inserted or removed from equipment in operation, or components that cannot become operable without affecting the operational state of that equipment, shall be indicated as not hot-pluggable.

IndicatorLED.longDescription: This property shall contain the indicator light state for the indicator light associated with this system.

enumDeprecated.Unknown: This value has been deprecated in favor of returning `null` if the state is unknown.

enumDescriptions.Unknown: The state of the indicator LED cannot be determined.

enumLongDescriptions.Blinking: This value shall represent the indicator LED is in a blinking state where the LED is being turned on and off in repetition. enumLongDescriptions.Off: This value shall represent the indicator LED is in a solid off state.  If the service does not support this value, it shall reject `PATCH` or `PUT` requests containing this value by returning the HTTP `400 Bad Request` status code.
enumLongDescriptions.Unknown: This value shall represent the indicator LED is in an unknown state.  The service shall reject `PATCH` or `PUT` requests containing this value by returning the HTTP `400 Bad Request` status code.
